==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palliard
<hw>Pal"liard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>paillard</ets>, orig., one addicted to the couch, fr.
<ets>paille</ets> straw. See <er>Pallet</er> a small bed.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A born beggar; a vagabond.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lecher; a lewd person.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palliasse</ent>⟦br⟧
